<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 2:28PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Appomattox, west central Buckingham, and southeastern Amherst
Counties and the northwestern City of Lynchburg through 300 PM EDT...
At 227 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Falconerville, or near Amherst, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Lynchburg...
Amherst...
Bent Creek...
Madison Heights...
Falconerville...
Riverville...
and New Glasgow.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
central and south central Virginia.</instruction>
